# RepoDoctor

**Automated technical documentation generator for code repositories using LLM analysis**

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/repodoctor.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/repodoctor)
[![Python versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/repodoctor.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/repodoctor/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

RepoDoctor analyzes your code repositories and generates comprehensive technical documentation using Large Language Model (LLM) analysis through OpenRouter API. It supports multiple programming languages and can output both Markdown documentation and beautiful Docusaurus websites.

## âœ¨ Features

- **ğŸ” Multi-language Analysis**: Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, C/C++, Rust, Go, and more
- **ğŸ“Š Dependency Extraction**: Automatic analysis of imports and module relationships  
- **ğŸ“š Structured Documentation**: Clean Markdown files with navigation
- **ğŸŒ Docusaurus Integration**: Generate modern documentation websites
- **âš¡ Parallel Processing**: Fast documentation generation with configurable workers
- **ğŸ¯ Smart Filtering**: Ignore patterns and hidden file handling
- **ğŸ”§ Professional CLI**: Easy-to-use command-line interface

## ğŸš€ Quick Start

### Installation

```bash
pip install repodoctor
```

### Setup API Key

RepoDoctor uses OpenRouter API for LLM analysis. Get your API key from [OpenRouter](https://openrouter.ai/) and set it:

```bash
export OPENROUTER_API_KEY="your-api-key-here"
```

Or create a `.env` file:
```bash
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your-api-key-here
```

### Basic Usage

```bash
# Generate documentation for a repository
repodoctor /path/to/your/project

# Generate with Docusaurus website
repodoctor /path/to/your/project --docusaurus

# Full automatic mode (generate + install + start)
repodoctor /path/to/your/project --docusaurus --auto-install --auto-start
```

## ğŸ“– Usage Examples

### Basic Documentation Generation

```bash
# Analyze current directory
repodoctor .

# Analyze specific project
repodoctor ../my-awesome-project

# Custom output directory
repodoctor /path/to/project --output ./project-docs

# Dry run to see what will be documented
repodoctor /path/to/project --dry-run
```

### Advanced Options

```bash
# More parallel workers for faster processing
repodoctor /path/to/project --workers 8

# Verbose logging
repodoctor /path/to/project --verbose

# Include hidden files in Docusaurus
repodoctor /path/to/project --docusaurus --docusaurus-show-hidden
```

### Docusaurus Website Generation

```bash
# Generate beautiful documentation website
repodoctor /path/to/project --docusaurus

# Auto-install dependencies and start dev server
repodoctor /path/to/project --docusaurus --auto-install --auto-start

# Manual Docusaurus setup (if not using --auto-install)
cd project-name-docusaurus/website
npm install
npm start
```

## ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture

RepoDoctor follows a clean, modular architecture:

```
repodoctor/
â”œâ”€â”€ __init__.py          # Package exports
â”œâ”€â”€ cli.py              # Command-line interface  
â”œâ”€â”€ generator.py        # Main documentation generator
â”œâ”€â”€ analyzer.py         # Code analysis and dependency extraction
â”œâ”€â”€ client.py           # OpenRouter API client
â””â”€â”€ docusaurus.py       # Docusaurus site generation
```

### Workflow

1. **ğŸ” Repository Scanning**: Discovers all supported code files
2. **ğŸ“Š Dependency Analysis**: Extracts imports and relationships
3. **ğŸ¤– LLM Analysis**: Generates documentation using AI
4. **ğŸ“ Markdown Creation**: Creates structured documentation files
5. **ğŸŒ Website Generation**: (Optional) Builds Docusaurus site

## ğŸ¯ Supported Languages

| Language | Extensions | Dependency Analysis |
|----------|------------|-------------------|
| Python | `.py` | âœ… (import, from) |
| JavaScript | `.js`, `.jsx` | âœ… (import, require) |
| TypeScript | `.ts`, `.tsx` | âœ… (import, require) |
| Java | `.java` | âœ… (import) |
| C/C++ | `.c`, `.cpp`, `.h`, `.hpp` | âœ… (#include) |
| Rust | `.rs` | âœ… (use) |
| Go | `.go` | âœ… (import) |
| Config Files | `.toml`, `.yaml`, `.json` | âœ… |
| Documentation | `.md`, `.txt` | âœ… |

## ğŸ“ Output Structure

### Markdown Documentation
```
docs/
â”œâ”€â”€ README.md                    # Project overview and navigation
â”œâ”€â”€ dependencies.md              # Dependency graph analysis
â”œâ”€â”€ file1.py.md                 # Individual file documentation
â”œâ”€â”€ file2.js.md                 # Preserves directory structure
â””â”€â”€ subdirectory/
    â””â”€â”€ module.py.md            # Nested files maintained
```

### Docusaurus Website
```
project-docusaurus/
â”œâ”€â”€ README.md                   # Setup instructions
â”œâ”€â”€ website/                    # Docusaurus project
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ docs/                  # Processed documentation
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ src/                   # React components
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ static/                # Static assets
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ docusaurus.config.ts   # Site configuration
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ sidebars.ts           # Navigation structure
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ package.json          # Dependencies
```

## âš™ï¸ Configuration

### Environment Variables

```bash
# Required
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...

# Optional
OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1  # Default OpenRouter endpoint
```

### CLI Options

```bash
repodoctor --help
```

| Option | Description | Default |
|--------|-------------|---------|
| `--output`, `-o` | Output directory | `{project}-docs-{uuid}` |
| `--workers`, `-w` | Parallel workers | `3` |
| `--api-key` | OpenRouter API key | From environment |
| `--verbose`, `-v` | Verbose logging | `False` |
| `--dry-run` | Preview without generating | `False` |
| `--docusaurus` | Generate Docusaurus site | `False` |
| `--auto-install` | Auto-install dependencies | `False` |
| `--auto-start` | Auto-start dev server | `False` |
| `--docusaurus-show-hidden` | Include hidden files | `False` |

## ğŸ”§ Programmatic Usage

```python
from repodoctor import DocumentationGenerator

# Initialize generator
generator = DocumentationGenerator(
    repo_path="/path/to/project",
    output_path="./docs",
    api_key="your-api-key"
)

# Generate documentation
generator.generate_documentation(
    max_workers=5,
    enable_docusaurus=True,
    auto_install=True,
    auto_start=True
)
```

## ğŸ› ï¸ Development

### Setup Development Environment

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/AlexanderOrlov/repodoctor.git
cd repodoctor

# Install in development mode
pip install -e .[dev]

# Run tests
pytest

# Format code
black repodoctor/
isort repodoctor/

# Type checking
mypy repodoctor/
```

### Building and Publishing

```bash
# Build package
python -m build

# Upload to PyPI (requires authentication)
python -m twine upload dist/*
```

